--- mlx_lm/server.py	2026-05-31 13:40:00
+++ mlx_lm/server.py	2026-05-31 14:01:00
@@ -404,10 +404,10 @@
         min_p=args.sampling.min_p,
         xtc_probability=args.sampling.xtc_probability,
         xtc_threshold=args.sampling.xtc_threshold,
         xtc_special_tokens=[
             tokenizer.eos_token_id,
-            tokenizer.encode("\n"),
+            *tokenizer.encode("\n"),
         ],
     )

# XTC is unusable through mlx_lm.server without this fix.
#
# NOTE: this is a KNOWN upstream bug, already reported and with fixes in flight (do
# NOT file a duplicate). Tracked as ml-explore/mlx-lm issue #1257; open fix PRs
# #1258, #1301 (also fixes int-param validation), and #1176 — none merged as of
# 2026-05-31. This local one-char patch is just to unblock our own runs until one
# of those lands. Our flatten is the same approach as #1176/#1258/#1301.
#
# tokenizer.encode("\n") returns a LIST of token ids (e.g. [201]), so the stock
# code builds a RAGGED xtc_special_tokens = [eos_id(int), [201](list)]. When
# apply_xtc() does `mask[..., xtc_special_tokens] = False`, MLX tries to build an
# index array from that ragged list and raises:
#     ValueError: Initialization encountered extra dimension.
# Every request that sets xtc_probability > 0 with temperature > 0 therefore 500s
# (the generation thread dies mid-stream -> "Remote end closed connection").
#
# This affects EVERY model served via mlx_lm.server, not just DeepSeek-V4 — any
# tokenizer where encode("\n") returns a list (all of them) hits it. The single
# `*` (splat) flattens the newline ids into the special-tokens list so it becomes
# a flat list of ints, which is what apply_xtc() expects (and what protects EOS +
# newline from being excluded by XTC). Verified on
# mlx-community/DeepSeek-V4-Flash-2bit-DQ: before -> 100% of XTC requests error;
# after -> XTC runs and reshapes the distribution as designed.
